From: "Jeanes, Matt" <JeanesM@advisory.com> Date: Fri, 6 Apr 2012 13:13:26 -0500 To: "Crimson Continuum of Care Cases" <CCC-cases@advisory.com> Cc: Subject: FW: UPI Loader Bug From: Jeanes, Matt Sent: Thursday, April 05, 2012 11:08 AM To: Eason, Linda Cc: McJilton, Josh; O'Keefe, Michael; Moin, Asad Subject: UPI Loader Bug
Linda, attached is a bug report for an issue that should already have been resolved. Asad tackled this once before, but we are seeing the problem again with Citadel. I can’t tell exactly what version of the CI code Citadel is invoking and frankly, I shouldn’t need to. Maybe this patch wasn’t applied to the version of the CI code that 2011.09 is running from Citadel? Maybe the patch was patched over with the old code? I don’t know. The end result is that UPI loader fails and I can’t move forward with my production load. Details are attached. Please let me know if you need anything else. If we can’t get this resolved today, please let me know so that I can hack my way around it. I hope that it’s as simple as finding the previously fixed code from Asad. I need to get this data loaded!
Thanks!
matt

From: Jeanes, Matt
Sent: Thursday, April 05, 2012 11:08 AM
To: Eason, Linda
Cc: McJilton, Josh; O'Keefe, Michael; Moin, Asad
Subject: UPI Loader Bug

 

Linda, attached is a bug report for an issue that should already have been resolved. Asad tackled this once before, but we are seeing the problem again with Citadel. I can’t tell exactly what version of the CI code Citadel is invoking and frankly, I shouldn’t need to. Maybe this patch wasn’t applied to the version of the CI code that 2011.09 is running from Citadel? Maybe the patch was patched over with the old code? I don’t know.  The end result is that UPI loader fails and I can’t move forward with my production load.  Details are attached. Please let me know if you need anything else. If we can’t get this resolved today, please let me know so that I can hack my way around it. I hope that it’s as simple as finding the previously fixed code from Asad. I need to get this data loaded!

 

Thanks!

matt
